1.title: What's To Lose?
1.plot: In this world debut episode of "Over The Rainbow" Web Series, Blyss has been hired for a new dog sitting via a new smartphone app for a couple leaving to go hottest spring break music festival in Southern California. While conversing with her roommate in the kitchen she discovers that he is is going to be leaving town during this same weekend. Blyss conspires to utilize this her apartment being empty during this time to create additional income.

2.title: Bogie & Nikki
2.plot: During the second episode of the season Blyss picks up Bogie from Nikki and her mother Fiona (played by Emmy Award winning actress Rolanda Mendelle) for dog sitting and Nikki heads off with her boyfriend Blaine to the hottest spring break music festival of the year in Southern California with her boyfriend. As Blyss begins to dog sit Bogie, she discovers that her roommate Alex isn't very fond of animals.

3.title: The Dog's Bark
3.plot: In "The Dog's Bark," on Season One of Over The Rainbow Web Series, Blyss checks in the guests from millennial vacay rentals and goes for a walk on the Venice Canals with her best friend Caity. Go to our You Tube Channel now to watch this episode and subscribe for updates.

4.title: A Bad Trip
4.plot: In "A Bad Trip," the fourth episode of "Over The Rainbow" Web Series Blyss faces several unanticipated challenges with her initial plan as she continues her second day of caring for Bogie and hosting for Millenial Vacay Rentals. Blyss later confronts Nikki's neighbor, who has made false accusations against Blyss, and catapults her weekend plans into a down spiral.

5.title: A Rough Night
5.plot: Bogie pees on Blyss while she is walking him, while Blyss (played by Miss California USA 2014 Contestant Suzanne Starr Smith) continues to struggle though her weekend money making scheme. Blyss decides to rely on her friends for help, but quickly discovers there are not many options as nearly everyone is away for the weekend in Palm Springs at the hottest music festival of spring break in California; So Cal Spring Break Fest. Fiona (played by Emmy Award Winning Actress Rolanda Mendelle) and the neighbor go to Nikki's and "rescue" Bogie from Blyss. Blyss becomes ...

6.title: Couch Surfing
6.plot: Blyss continues to deliver food and host for Millenial Vacay Rentals and is able to navigate through the unexpected chaos of the weekend- and learn to survive in the big city in ways that most people never even have to consider. The Millenial Vacay rental girls have a blast at the "beach cottage."

7.title: Weekend Warrior
7.plot: In the final episode of season one, Blyss enjoys her morning with Melissa, and finally goes home. When she arrives there is an awkward run in with Alex. Blyss submerges into a hot bubble bath to melt the stress of the weekend away and enjoys being back in the comfort of her own home.

imdb.plot outline: A hilarious web series featuring an alluring cast including an Emmy winning actress, as well as music from a Grammy nominated artist. Blyss is on the roller coaster of life, and constantly is exploring new experiences; as well as seeming to live in a world of juxtaposition....While experiencing the freedom and struggles of being a young, independent woman in the big city-she is constantly discovering new ways to thrive and survive as she is on the brink of living her dream of being a working, successful performing artist and finding her true destiny. In "Over The Rainbow: Season One," Blyss experiments during the weekend of Southern California's biggest music festival weekend of the season with profiting off all of the new phone apps developed in Silicon Beach to get ahead in life, yet instead she finds herself in a whirlwind of chaos.
